017package org.apache.juneau.bean.html5;

019import org.apache.juneau.annotation.*;

022/**
023 * DTO for an HTML <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/text-level-semantics.html#the-sub-and-sup-elements">&lt;sup&gt;</a>
024 * element.
025 *
026 * <p>
027 * The sup element represents superscript text. It is used to display text that should be rendered
028 * above the baseline, typically in a smaller font size. The sup element is commonly used for
029 * mathematical formulas, footnotes, ordinal numbers, and other annotations that need to be
030 * displayed as superscript.
031 *
032 * <h5 class='section'>Examples:</h5>
033 * <p class='bcode w800'>
034 *    <jk>import static</jk> org.apache.juneau.bean.html5.HtmlBuilder.*;
035 *
036 *    <jc>// Mathematical formula</jc>
037 *    Sup <jv>math</jv> = <jsm>sup</jsm>(
038 *       <js>"x"</js>, <jsm>sup</jsm>(<js>"2"</js>),
039 *       <js>" + y"</js>, <jsm>sup</jsm>(<js>"2"</js>),
040 *       <js>" = z"</js>, <jsm>sup</jsm>(<js>"2"</js>)
041 *    );
042 *
043 *    <jc>// Ordinal numbers</jc>
044 *    Sup <jv>ordinal</jv> = <jsm>sup</jsm>(<js>"1st"</js>, <jsm>sup</jsm>(<js>"st"</js>));
045 *
046 *    <jc>// Footnote reference</jc>
047 *    Sup <jv>footnote</jv> = <jsm>sup</jsm>(<js>"1"</js>);
048 *
049 *    <jc>// Superscript with styling</jc>
050 *    Sup <jv>styled</jv> = <jsm>sup</jsm>(<js>"n"</js>)
051 *       ._class(<js>"superscript"</js>);
052 *
053 *    <jc>// Multiple superscripts</jc>
054 *    Sup <jv>multiple</jv> = <jsm>sup</jsm>(
055 *       <js>"A"</js>, <jsm>sup</jsm>(<js>"i,j"</js>),
056 *       <js>" = B"</js>, <jsm>sup</jsm>(<js>"k"</js>)
057 *    );
058 * </p>
059 *
060 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
061 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanHtml5">juneau-bean-html5</a>
062 * </ul>
063 */
064@Bean(typeName="sup")
065public class Sup extends HtmlElementMixed {
066
067   /**
068    * Creates an empty {@link Sup} element.
069    */
070   public Sup() {}
071
072   /**
073    * Creates a {@link Sup} element with the specified child nodes.
074    *
075    * @param children The child nodes.
076    */
077   public Sup(Object...children) {
078      children(children);
079   }
